-- UBS Said to Plan Covered Bonds Backed by Prime Swiss Home Loans
-- B y   P a u l   A r m s t r o n g
-- 2011-12-30T10:21:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-30/ubs-said-to-plan-sale-of-covered-bonds-backed-by-prime-swiss-home-loans.html
UBS AG (UBSN)  hired banks for a planned
sale of covered bonds denominated in euros and backed by prime
Swiss residential mortgages, according to a banker and investor
familiar with the matter.  UBS plans to sell the bonds early in 2012 depending on
market conditions, the people said. As well as its own
investment-banking unit, UBS hired BNP Paribas SA, Commerzbank
AG, ING Groep NV, Natixis and  UniCredit SpA (UCG)  to manage the deal,
which is likely to have top ratings from Moodyâ€™s Investors
Service and Fitch Ratings, the people said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
